## MCP Integration (Optional)

When the OmniCursor MCP server is available, enhance this rule with structured backend support:

1. **At the start of the session**, call `get_agent_context` with `category="planning"` to receive routing instructions and the recommended skill name.
2. **If deeper methodology is needed**, call `invoke_skill` with `skill_name="writing-plans"` to load the full skill workflow document.
3. **After producing the final plan**, call `check_compliance` with `skill_name="writing-plans"` and a summary of what was produced. Review any missing checks and address them before handing off.

These MCP calls are optional enhancements. The rule works without them — the preserved methodology above is the primary workflow.
